In the above graph we see that the data is skewed to the right. So we will apply log transformation to the x axis. We see bi modal distribution in our graph.

##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.

##   0.900   1.900   2.200   2.539   2.600  15.500

The graph above shows it is skewed to right. We will apply log transformation.

I will create a new variable called quality.factor which will be helpful in plotting box plots . Since quality it is a continous variable we will make the new variable as factor var.

Univariate Analysis

Structure of the dataset. There are 1599 observation with 13 variables (x,fixed.acidity,volatile.acidity,citric.acid,residual.sugar,chlorides,free.sulphur.dioxide,density,pH,sulphates,alcohol,quality).X and quality are int variable and rest of the variables are num.

Other observations:

quality has minimum value of 3. Median is 6. Mean is 5.635, MAx is 8. The count of density is more with density value from 0.996 to 0.997 residual sugar has median value as 2.200,mean is 2.539. But the max value is 15.500 which seems to be an outlier in the data. fixed.acidity has median value as 7.90,mean as 8.32, but the max value os 15.90 which is an outlier.

Main feature(s) of interest in dataset

The main feature of interest in your dataset is to observe the quality of the red wine.Also how other factors like alcohol,pH,residual sugar affect the quality of the red wine.

Other features in the dataset I think will help support my investigation into the feature(s) of interest?

Fixed.acidity,volatile.acidity and citric.acid are other features that may help in investigation

Create any new variables from existing variables in the dataset

New variable created is :: redwinedf$quality.factor

Unusual distributions.Operation performed to change distribution.

Alcohol was skewed to the right. So I applied lox_x transformation and observed a bimodal distribution. residual sugar was skewed to the right. After applying log_x transformation it changed into a normal distribution.

Bivariate Analysis

Alcohol,citric acid and suplhates are strongly co related to quality. Fixed acidity is slightly co related to quality. It can be seen from the above graph.

Interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?

We see that there is strong relationship between free.sulphur.dioxide and total.sulphur.dioxide.

Strongest relationship.

Strongest correlation between free.sulfur.dioxide and total.sulfur.dioxide. Second co relation is beween alcohol and quality.

Multivariate Plots Section

It is clear from the above graph that the quality is determined by the content of alcohol

## Warning: Removed 16 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Alcohol, citric acid and Sulphate are strongly related to quality in a linear way.As the value of the three variables increases the quality of the alcohol increases.

From the above observation we see that quality of the alcohol increases with the decrease in volatile.acidity.So there is non linear relationship.

Multivariate Analysis

Relationship between the variables.

Relationship between quality and alcohol shows strong relationship between the two variables.

alcohol - Strong linear pH - Slight Non linear residual sugar - flat fixed.acidity - slight linear volatile.acidity - Strong non linear citric.acid - Strong linear chlorides - Slight non linear (close to flat) free.sulfur.dioxide - Slight non linear (close to flat) total sulphur dioxide - Non linear Sulphates - Strong linear density - Non linear

Reflection

I performed Univariate, bivariate and Multivariate analysis for the redwine dataset. I also created various visualization graphs like histogram, box plots and Scatter plots as part of our exploratory data analysis process.Explored the variables and observed relationship between the variables. Variables like alcohol,citric.acid and sulphates have strong linear relationship with quality variable.There are some variables which has non linear relationship with the quality variable like pH,volatile.acidity and sulphates.

In our Final plots and Summary section all the variables can be observed in the graph. After exploring the dataset I observed that the data poins are distributed equally due to which we cannot make a significant decision about the dataset. More data may be required to find a strong pattern in data. Then we can create a predictive model to determine the quality of the alcohol based on various inputs.
